According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Unmanned Ground Vehicle (UGV) market was valued at USD 0.62 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 0.66 billion in 2026 to USD 1.12 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.1% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing significant momentum due to rising defense modernization programs across Europe, increasing investments in autonomous military technologies, and expanding adoption of UGVs in commercial sectors such as logistics, mining, agriculture, and infrastructure inspection. Advancements in artificial intelligence, sensor fusion, and edge computing are further enhancing vehicle autonomy, while collaborative initiatives under NATO and the EU's Permanent Structured Cooperation (PESCO) are accelerating innovation and deployment across the region.
